The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence at the swearing-in ceremony of Dr. Jerome Adams as the 20th Surgeon General of the United States. Pence welcomed Adams and praised his qualifications and experience as a physician and public servant. He also acknowledged the presence of other distinguished guests, including Secretary of Health and Human Services Tom Price and various representatives from the medical community. Pence emphasized President Trump's commitment to addressing urgent health challenges, such as the opioid epidemic and infectious diseases. He expressed confidence that Adams' leadership and values will bring hope and healing to the nation. Adams thanked the President and Vice President for the opportunity to serve, and highlighted the importance of partnerships in improving public health. He outlined his priorities, including addressing the opioid epidemic, mental health, and childhood obesity, and called for partnerships between the health and law enforcement communities. Adams also expressed gratitude to his family, friends, and mentors for their support.